A photo it is said makes more than a thousand words. Could you say a thousand words about the view out of your window? I can, you probably can doit to and that's maybe because you know what you are looking at and understand the reality out there, to a certain degree. The ongoing motion, the space, the time, by having yourself a place in it, behind the window.

Looking at a photography is somewhat like looking trough a window, only that your place in relation to it and the ongoing narrative is not always so evident. But after some thinking we make sense of it and then we can maybe say it makes more than a thousand words.

READMORE

How about abstract photography? It's of a different nature; it sends the viewer on a journey it stimulates the imagination, it is a beast unchained... a phantom that hunts you and eludes your reason. 
You can feel in a certain way about it, like it, not like it, fell in love with or hate it. Abstract doesn't make you reason it plays on emotion, it makes you feel a certain way. This is why I use it sometime in my work, for the effect.

