The designer has the power to controlled how the message is emphasied, parts of it can be amplified with highly articulate meaning while others let loose. The beauty is in the harmonious alternance of these two states, the effectiveness is given by the interplay between abstract and  concrete.

Lately I become very fond of abstract photography and made a little collection of them - an ongoing exploration to call it so. These images are taken (and sometimes edited) with my phone, a HTC m8. I gladly make this available for everybody to use as they wish in their graphic design work.

Give credit if you want or reach me out on twitter [@nedzen](http://www.twitter.com/@nedzen)

See more on flickr in the [Experiments album](https://flic.kr/s/aHsknqNTx1). I hope these example makes you look closer next time you see abstract images used in design work.

